<item>
            <title>[HBASE-955] Stop HLog thread before starting a new one</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-955</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, when we encounter a MSG_CALL_SERVER_STARTUP situation in the master the region server discards the old HLog for a new one. However, it does not stop the thread associated with the old HLog. Thus we have an orphaned thread doing nothing, except consuming CPU. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12407206">HBASE-955</key>
