                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12642552" author="stack" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2008 22:03:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-728&quot; title=&quot;Supporting for HLog appends&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-728&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-728&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643062" author="jimk" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2008 21:13:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will be not applicable after upcoming patch to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-728&quot; title=&quot;Supporting for HLog appends&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-728&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-728&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, because HLog will no longer be either a Thread or a Chore. Instead a HLog object will manage the HLog and nothing else.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;LogRoller, (a Thread) and LogFlusher (a Chore) will be responsible for getting the HLog to disk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12643068" author="jimk" created="Mon, 27 Oct 2008 21:33:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
